  "prompt": "I temporarily deactivated my instagram, when I try to log in it says I should try again in a few hours. How long does it take to reactivate it?",
  "response": "When you temporarily deactivate your Instagram account, you should typically be able to reactivate it immediately by simply logging back in. However, if you're receiving a message that says to try again in a few hours, it may be due to a verification or security measure from Instagram. This can sometimes happen if there's unusual activity detected on your account.\n\nIn most cases, waiting a few hours should resolve the issue, and you can try logging in again later. If you continue to experience problems after that time, you might want to try clearing your app cache, using a different device, or reaching out to Instagram support for assistance.",
